      "writtenOn": "2026-06-02T05:32:31Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I apologize for that mistake. I should not have\ninvented xyz.openbmc_project.Sensor.State as an interface.\n\nI\u0027ve replaced it with the correct PDI decorator interfaces:\n- xyz.openbmc_project.State.Decorator.OperationalStatus (tracks functional status)\n- xyz.openbmc_project.State.Decorator.Availability (tracks sensor availability)\n\nBoth are standard decorators defined in phosphor-dbus-interfaces and are the\nappropriate choice for this use case. Thank you for the correction.",
      "parentUuid": "a2f3ec64_924dc1ac",
